{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585707","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585707"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:16:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:16:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15004"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15004","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15004"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.29,0.13,0.21,0.38]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7692"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66746"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7692"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15004"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52200"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"176"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3764"},{"type":"tags","id":"4908"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5440"},{"type":"tags","id":"7875"},{"type":"tags","id":"11140"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18798"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18805"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66746","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66746"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old woman presents with bone pain and fatigue. Initial investigations suggest multiple myeloma.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following laboratory techniques is most appropriate for detecting monoclonal proteins?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Immunonephelometry","Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay","Flow cytometry","Immunofluorescence microscopy","Serum protein electrophoresis"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum protein electrophoresis\u003C/strong\u003E is the gold standard screening test for detecting monoclonal proteins (M-proteins). This technique separates proteins based on their electrical charge and size, producing a characteristic spike in the gamma region when monoclonal immunoglobulins are present.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other techniques are less suitable:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunonephelometry\u003C/strong\u003E measures total immunoglobulin levels but cannot distinguish between monoclonal and polyclonal proteins\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnzyme-linked immunosorbent assay\u003C/strong\u003E detects specific antigens but cannot identify monoclonal proteins\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlow cytometry\u003C/strong\u003E analyses cellular components and surface markers, not serum proteins\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunofluorescence microscopy\u003C/strong\u003E detects specific antibodies or antigens but cannot effectively characterise monoclonal gammopathies\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter identifying an M-protein spike, immunofixation electrophoresis can determine the specific immunoglobulin type involved.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Serum protein electrophoresis is the primary screening test for detecting monoclonal gammopathies in multiple myeloma","Electrophoresis separates proteins based on their electrical charge and molecular size, revealing characteristic M-protein spikes","The presence of an M-protein spike in the gamma region is diagnostic of monoclonal gammopathy"],"references":["Tripathy S. The role of serum protein electrophoresis in the detection of multiple myeloma: an experience of a corporate hospital. J Clin Diagn Res. 2012 Nov;6(9):1458-61. doi: 10.7860/JCDR/2012/4213.2532. PMID: 23285429; PMCID: PMC3527769.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52200"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15004"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52200","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52200"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T20:53:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T20:56:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7692"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66746"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relatio